25|$|Whether {{this right}} {{is caused by}} {{horizontal}} effect of the Human Rights Act 1998 or is judicially created {{is a matter of}} some controversy. <b>The</b> <b>right</b> <b>to</b> <b>privacy</b> is protected by Article 8 of the convention. In the context of photography, it stands at odds to the Article 10 right of freedom of expression. As such, courts will consider the public interest in balancing the rights through the legal test of proportionality.|$|E
